--('GEN',  13,   2, 'Abram was very rich in livestock, in silver, and in gold.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 10, 'Now the valley of Siddim was full of tar pits; and the kings of Sodom and Gomorrah fled, and they fell there, and those who remained fled to the hills.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,   3, 'He went on his journeys from the South as far as Bethel, to the place where his tent had been at the beginning, between Bethel and Ai,'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 11, 'They took all the goods of Sodom and Gomorrah, and all their food, and went their way.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,   4, 'to the place of the altar, which he had made there at the first. There Abram called on TheIAM<H3068>\'s name.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 12, 'They took Lot, Abram\'s brother\'s son, who lived in Sodom, and his goods, and departed.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,   5, 'Lot also, who went with Abram, had flocks, herds, and tents.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 13, 'One who had escaped came and told Abram, the Hebrew. Now he lived by the oaks of Mamre, the Amorite, brother of Eshcol, and brother of Aner; and these were allies<H1167> of Abram.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,   6, 'The land was not able to bear them, that they might live together; for their possessions were so great that they couldn\'t live together.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 14, 'When Abram heard that his relative was taken captive, he led forth his trained men, born in his house, three hundred and eighteen, and pursued<H7291> as far as Dan.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,   7, 'There was strife between the herdsmen of Abram\'s livestock and the herdsmen of Lot\'s livestock. The Canaanites and the Perizzites lived in the land at that time.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 15, 'He divided himself against them by night, he and his servants, and struck them, and pursued<H7291> them to Hobah, which is on the left hand of Damascus.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,   8, 'Abram said to Lot, \"Please, let there be no strife between you and me, and between your herdsmen and my herdsmen; for we are relatives.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 16, 'He brought back all the goods, and also brought back his relative, Lot, and his goods, and the women also, and the people.');
--('GEN',  13,   9, 'Isn\'t the whole land before you? Please separate yourself from me. If you go to the left hand, then I will go to the right. Or if you go to the right hand, then I will go to the left.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 17, 'The king of Sodom went out to meet him, after his return from the slaughter of Chedorlaomer and the kings who were with him, at the valley of Shaveh (that is, the King\'s Valley).');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,  10, 'Lot lifted up his eyes, and saw all the plain of the Jordan, that it was well-watered everywhere, before TheIAM<H3068> destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah, like the garden of TheIAM<H3068>, like the land of Egypt, as you go to Zoar.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 18, 'Melchizedek king of Salem brought out bread and wine: and he was priest of God<H0410> Most High.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,  11, 'So Lot chose the Plain of the Jordan for himself. Lot traveled east, and they separated themselves from one other.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 19, 'He blessed him, and said, \"Blessed be Abram of God<H0410> Most High, possessor of heaven and earth:');
--('GEN',  13,  12, 'Abram lived in the land of Canaan, and Lot lived in the cities of the plain, and moved his tent as far as Sodom.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 20, 'and blessed be God<H0410> Most High, who has delivered your enemies into your hand.\" Abram gave him a tenth of all.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,  13, 'Now the men of Sodom were exceedingly wicked and sinners against TheIAM<H3068>.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 21, 'The king of Sodom said to Abram, \"Give me the people, and take the goods to yourself.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,  14, 'TheIAM<H3068> said to Abram, after Lot was separated from him, \"Now, lift up your eyes, and look from the place where you are, northward and southward and eastward and westward,'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 22, 'Abram said to the king of Sodom, \"I have lifted up my hand to TheIAM<H3068>, God<H0410> Most High, possessor of heaven and earth,');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,  15, 'for I will give all the land which you see to you and to your offspring forever.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 23, 'that I will not take a thread nor a sandal strap nor anything that is yours, lest you should say, \'I have made Abram rich.\'');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,  16, 'I will make your offspring as the dust of the earth, so that if a man can count the dust of the earth, then your offspring may also be counted.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 14, 24, 'I will accept nothing from you except that which the young men have eaten, and the portion of the men who went with me: Aner, Eshcol, and Mamre. Let them take their portion.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,  17, 'Arise, walk through the land in its length and in its width; for I will give it to you.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 1, 'After these things the word of TheIAM<H3068> came to Abram in a vision, saying, \"Don\'t be afraid, Abram. I am your shield, your exceedingly great reward.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  13,  18, 'Abram moved his tent, and came and lived by the oaks of Mamre, which are in Hebron, and built an altar there to TheIAM<H3068>.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 2, 'Abram said, \"Lord<H0136> TheIAM<H3068>, what will you give me, since I go childless, and he who will inherit my estate is Eliezer of Damascus?\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,   1, 'In the days of Amraphel, king of Shinar; Arioch, king of Ellasar; Chedorlaomer, king of Elam; and Tidal, king of Goiim,'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 3, 'Abram said, \"Behold, to me you have given no seed: and, behold, one born in my house is my heir.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,   2, 'they made war with Bera, king of Sodom; Birsha, king of Gomorrah; Shinab, king of Admah; Shemeber, king of Zeboiim; and the king of Bela (also called Zoar).'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 4, 'Behold, the word of TheIAM<H3068> came to him, saying, \"This man will not be your heir, but he who will come forth out of your own body will be your heir.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,   3, 'All these joined together in the valley of Siddim (also called the Salt Sea).'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 5, 'TheIAM<H3068> brought him outside, and said, \"Look now toward the sky, and count the stars, if you are able to count them.\" He said to Abram, \"So shall your seed be.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,   4, 'They served Chedorlaomer for twelve years, and in the thirteenth year they rebelled.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 6, 'He believed in TheIAM<H3068>; and he reckoned it to him for righteousness.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,   5, 'In the fourteenth year Chedorlaomer and the kings who were with him came and struck the Rephaim in Ashteroth Karnaim, the Zuzim in Ham, the Emim in Shaveh Kiriathaim,'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 7, 'He said to him, \"I am TheIAM<H3068> who brought you out of Ur of the Chaldees, to give you this land to inherit it.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,   6, 'and the Horites in their Mount Seir, to El Paran, which is by the wilderness.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 8, 'He said, \"Lord<H0136> TheIAM<H3068>, how will I know that I will inherit it?\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,   7, 'They returned, and came to En Mishpat (also called Kadesh), and struck all the country of the Amalekites, and also the Amorites, that lived in Hazazon Tamar.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 9, 'He said to him, \"Bring me a heifer three years old, a female goat three years old, a ram three years old, a turtledove, and a young pigeon.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,   8, 'The king of Sodom, and the king of Gomorrah, the king of Admah, the king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (also called Zoar) went out; and they set the battle in array against them in the valley of Siddim'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 10, 'He brought him all of these, and divided them in the middle, and laid each half opposite the other; but he didn\'t divide the birds.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,   9, 'against Chedorlaomer king of Elam, Tidal king of Goiim, Amraphel king of Shinar, and Arioch king of Ellasar; four kings against the five.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 11, 'The birds of prey came down on the carcasses, and Abram drove them away.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  10, 'Now the valley of Siddim was full of tar pits; and the kings of Sodom and Gomorrah fled, and some fell there. Those who remained fled to the hills.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 12, 'When the sun was going down, a deep sleep fell on Abram. Now terror and great darkness fell on him.');
--('GEN',  14,  11, 'They took all the goods of Sodom and Gomorrah, and all their food, and went their way.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 13, 'He said to Abram, \"Know for sure that your seed will live as foreigners in a land that is not theirs, and will serve them. They will afflict them four hundred years.');
--('GEN',  14,  12, 'They took Lot, Abram\'s brother\'s son, who lived in Sodom, and his goods, and departed.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 14, 'I will also judge that nation, whom they will serve. Afterward they will come out with great wealth,');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  13, 'One who had escaped came and told Abram, the Hebrew. At that time, he lived by the oaks of Mamre, the Amorite, brother of Eshcol and brother of Aner. They were allies of Abram.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 15, 'but you will go to your fathers in peace. You will be buried in a good old age.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  14, 'When Abram heard that his relative was taken captive, he led out his three hundred eighteen trained men, born in his house, and pursued as far as Dan.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 16, 'In the fourth generation they will come here again, for the iniquity of the Amorite is not yet full.\"');
--('GEN',  14,  15, 'He divided himself against them by night, he and his servants, and struck them, and pursued<H7291> them to Hobah, which is on the left hand of Damascus.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 17, 'It came to pass that, when the sun went down, and it was dark, behold, a smoking furnace, and a flaming torch passed between these pieces.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  16, 'He brought back all the goods, and also brought back his relative Lot and his goods, and the women also, and the other people.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 18, 'In that day TheIAM<H3068> made a covenant with Abram, saying, \"To your seed I have given this land, from the river of Egypt to the great river, the river Euphrates:');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  17, 'The king of Sodom went out to meet him after his return from the slaughter of Chedorlaomer and the kings who were with him, at the valley of Shaveh (that is, the King\'s Valley).'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 19, 'the Kenites, the Kenizzites, the Kadmonites,');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  18, 'Melchizedek king of Salem brought out bread and wine. He was priest of God<H0430> Most High.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 20, 'the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Rephaim,');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  19, 'He blessed him, and said, \"Blessed be Abram of God<H0430> Most High, possessor of heaven and earth.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 15, 21, 'the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  20, 'Blessed be God<H0430> Most High, who has delivered your enemies into your hand.\" Abram gave him a tenth of all.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 1, 'Now Sarai, Abram\'s wife, bore him no children. She had a handmaid, an Egyptian, whose name was Hagar.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  21, 'The king of Sodom said to Abram, \"Give me the people, and take the goods for yourself.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 2, 'Sarai said to Abram, \"See now, TheIAM<H3068> has restrained me from bearing. Please go in to my handmaid. It may be that I will obtain children by her.\" Abram listened to the voice of Sarai.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  14,  22, 'Abram said to the king of Sodom, \"I have lifted up my hand to TheIAM<H3068>, God<H0430> Most High, possessor of heaven and earth,'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 3, 'Sarai, Abram\'s wife, took Hagar the Egyptian, her handmaid, after Abram had lived ten years in the land of Canaan, and gave her to Abram her husband to be his wife.');
--('GEN',  14,  23, 'that I will not take a thread nor a sandal strap nor anything that is yours, lest you should say, \'I have made Abram rich.\'');
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 4, 'He went in to Hagar, and she conceived. When she saw that she had conceived, her mistress was despised in her eyes.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 5, 'Sarai said to Abram, \"This wrong is your fault. I gave my handmaid into your bosom, and when she saw that she had conceived, I was despised in her eyes. TheIAM<H3068> judge between me and you.\"');
--('GEN',  14,  24, 'I will accept nothing from you except that which the young men have eaten, and the portion of the men who went with me: Aner, Eshcol, and Mamre. Let them take their portion.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 6, 'But Abram said to Sarai, \"Behold, your maid is in your hand. Do to her whatever is good in your eyes.\" Sarai dealt harshly with her, and she fled from her face.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,   1, 'After these things TheIAM<H3068>\'s word came to Abram in a vision, saying, \"Don\'t be afraid, Abram. I am your shield, your exceedingly great reward.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 7, 'The angel of TheIAM<H3068> found her by a fountain of water in the wilderness, by the fountain in the way to Shur.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,   2, 'Abram said, \"Lord<H0113> TheIAM<H3068>, what will you give me, since I go childless, and he who will inherit my estate is Eliezer of Damascus?\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 8, 'He said, \"Hagar, Sarai\'s handmaid, where did you come from? Where are you going?\" She said, \"I am fleeing from the face of my mistress Sarai.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,   3, 'Abram said, \"Behold, you have given no children to me: and, behold, one born in my house is my heir.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 9, 'The angel of TheIAM<H3068> said to her, \"Return to your mistress, and submit yourself under her hands.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,   4, 'Behold, TheIAM<H3068>\'s word came to him, saying, \"This man will not be your heir, but he who will come out of your own body will be your heir.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 10, 'The angel of TheIAM<H3068> said to her, \"I will greatly multiply your seed, that they will not be numbered for multitude.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,   5, 'TheIAM<H3068> brought him outside, and said, \"Look now toward the sky, and count the stars, if you are able to count them.\" He said to Abram, \"So your offspring will be.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 11, 'The angel of TheIAM<H3068> said to her, \"Behold, you are with child, and will bear a son. You shall call his name Ishmael, because TheIAM<H3068> has heard your affliction.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,   6, 'He believed in TheIAM<H3068>, who credited it to him for righteousness.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 12, 'He will be like a wild donkey among men. His hand will be against every man, and every man\'s hand against him. He will live opposite all of his brothers.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,   7, 'He said to Abram, \"I am TheIAM<H3068> who brought you out of Ur of the Chaldees, to give you this land to inherit it.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 13, 'She called the name of TheIAM<H3068> who spoke to her, \"You are a God<H0410> who sees,\" for she said, \"Have I even stayed alive after seeing him?\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,   8, 'He said, \"Lord<H0113> TheIAM<H3068>, how will I know that I will inherit it?\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 14, 'Therefore the well was called Beer Lahai Roi. Behold, it is between Kadesh and Bered.');
--('GEN',  15,   9, 'He said to him, \"Bring me a heifer three years old, a female goat three years old, a ram three years old, a turtledove, and a young pigeon.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 15, 'Hagar bore a son for Abram. Abram called the name of his son, whom Hagar bore, Ishmael.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,  10, 'He brought him all these, and divided them in the middle, and laid each half opposite the other; but he didn\'t divide the birds.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 16, 16, 'Abram was eighty-six years old when Hagar bore Ishmael to Abram.');
--('GEN',  15,  11, 'The birds of prey came down on the carcasses, and Abram drove them away.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 1, 'When Abram was ninety-nine years old, TheIAM<H3068> appeared to Abram, and said to him, \"I am God<H0410> Almighty<H7706>. Walk before me, and be blameless.');
--('GEN',  15,  12, 'When the sun was going down, a deep sleep fell on Abram. Now terror and great darkness fell on him.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 2, 'I will make my covenant between me and you, and will multiply you exceedingly.\"');
--('GEN',  15,  13, 'He said to Abram, \"Know for sure that your offspring will live as foreigners in a land that is not theirs, and will serve them. They will afflict them four hundred years.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 3, 'Abram fell on his face. God<H0430> talked with him, saying,');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,  14, 'I will also judge that nation, whom they will serve. Afterward they will come out with great wealth;'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 4, '\"As for me, behold, my covenant is with you. You will be the father of a multitude of nations.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,  15, 'but you will go to your fathers in peace. You will be buried at a good old age.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 5, 'Neither will your name any more be called Abram, but your name will be Abraham; for I have made you the father of a multitude of nations.');
--('GEN',  15,  16, 'In the fourth generation they will come here again, for the iniquity of the Amorite is not yet full.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 6, 'I will make you exceedingly fruitful, and I will make nations of you. Kings will come out of you.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,  17, 'It came to pass that, when the sun went down, and it was dark, behold, a smoking furnace and a flaming torch passed between these pieces.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 7, 'I will establish my covenant between me and you and your seed after you throughout their generations for an everlasting covenant, to be a God<H0430> to you and to your seed after you.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,  18, 'In that day TheIAM<H3068> made a covenant with Abram, saying, \"I have given this land to your offspring, from the river of Egypt to the great river, the river Euphrates:'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 8, 'I will give to you, and to your seed after you, the land where you are traveling, all the land of Canaan, for an everlasting possession. I will be their God<H0430>.\"');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  15,  19, 'the land of the Kenites, the Kenizzites, the Kadmonites,'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 9, 'God<H0430> said to Abraham, \"As for you, you will keep my covenant, you and your seed after you throughout their generations.');
--('GEN',  15,  20, 'the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Rephaim,'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 10, 'This is my covenant, which you shall keep, between me and you and your seed after you. Every male among you shall be circumcised.');
--('GEN',  15,  21, 'the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.\"'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 11, 'You shall be circumcised in the flesh of your foreskin. It will be a token of the covenant between me and you.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  16,   1, 'Now Sarai, Abram\'s wife, bore him no children. She had a servant, an Egyptian, whose name was Hagar.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 12, 'He who is eight days old will be circumcised among you, every male throughout your generations, he who is born in the house, or bought with money from any foreigner who is not of your seed.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  16,   2, 'Sarai said to Abram, \"See now, TheIAM<H3068> has restrained me from bearing. Please go in to my servant. It may be that I will obtain children by her.\" Abram listened to the voice of Sarai.'),
INSERT INTO verses (bookCode, chapter, verseNumber, verseText) VALUES('GEN', 17, 13, 'He who is born in your house, and he who is bought with your money, must be circumcised. My covenant will be in your flesh for an everlasting covenant.');
--INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GEN',  16,   3, 'Sarai, Abram\'s wife, took Hagar the Egyptian, her servant, after Abram had lived ten years in the land of Canaan, and gave her to Abram her husband to be his wife.'),
